> The Beck/Tews WiFi WPA attack presented at PacSec has been improved (down to 1
> min, MITM) by 2 .jp researchers (Ohigashi, Morii) http://bit.ly/clCpm
> Remember: avoid WPA/TKIP and force AES only encryption in WPA2 - don't let
> your access point automatically fall back automatically to the insecure
> TKIP/WPA mode, to be safe. (At least until any WPA2 attacks are published ;-P)
> 
